Filename   Port      Description  46C521  WriteBack  (486DLC retrofit)
--------   -------   ---------------------------------------------------------
V082B430   FORX420   386/486/Cyrix '521
V082B431   FORX421   x082B430  (T-)
V082B432   FORX422   x082b430  (T+)
V082B433   FORX423   x082b430  (CL-)        <-- demo board
V082B434   FORX424   x082b430  (CL+)

Note - Vers 430-434  fully support Cyrix 486DLC in 386 socket
       without any special hardware considerations for it.  (To
       maintain cache coherence, Cyrix CCR0 "BARB" is set, &tc).


Filename   Port      Description  46C521  WriteBack (486DLC design-in)
--------   -------   ---------------------------------------------------------
V082B435   FORX425   386/486/Cyrix '521
V082B436   FORX426   x082B435  (T-)
V082B437   FORX427   x082b435  (T+)
V082B438   FORX428   x082b435  (CL-)
V082B439   FORX429   x082b435  (CL+)

Note - Vers 435-439  require specific design-in considerations for
       Cyrix 486DLC.  These pins must be connected: #FLUSH, #KEN, #A20M.

       These versions give best Cyrix performance (compared with "retrofit"
       versions), but will MALFUNCTION unless the board is designed for it.


